The paper discusses the use of logic and programming to solve search problems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes two logics based on predicate calculus, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The use of logic programming and the semantics of stable models is also mentioned, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the development of computational tools for model finding, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
